1
00:00:16,141 --> 00:00:18,727
Nice, nice! Sparks are flying!

2
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:20,770
<i>What's so nice about this?</i>

3
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:24,190
But, Sakura-kun,
when you're in front of Sugishita-san...

4
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:28,611
you really shouldn't have said
"I came here to be the top."

5
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:30,613
You bastard.

6
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:34,075
Sugishita-kun has been visiting here
since he was in middle school,

7
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:36,703
and after his passion and talents
were recognized,

8
00:00:36,786 --> 00:00:41,708
he was allowed to call himself a part of
Bofurin before he even got to high school.

9
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:46,588
What's more, his extreme loyalty
to our current top, or rather,

10
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:53,219
his worship of him
makes him a fanatic to the...

11
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:58,975
And here you are,
saying you'll usurp him, so yeah.

12
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,102
Don't just stir things up! Stop him!

13
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:03,354
Me? Why don't you stop them, then?

14
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:04,856
We can't!

15
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:09,235
If you don't stop him,
he'll kill that outsider!

16
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:16,576
Too bad, you missed.

17
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:26,836
A fanatic, eh?

18
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,839
That means you can't think for yourself

19
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:32,967
or decide anything on your own, right?

20
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:37,263
As if I'd lose to a guy like that!

21
00:03:17,196 --> 00:03:18,948
Sakura-san.

22
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:25,204
<i>One, two. One, two. Testing, testing.</i>

23
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:29,459
<i>Which button am I supposed to press?</i>

24
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:33,004
<i>What? It's already on?
Why didn't you say anything?</i>

25
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:34,005
<i>I did!</i>

26
00:03:34,088 --> 00:03:35,506
What the hell?

27
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:40,762
<i>Welcome, all new students!</i>

28
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:43,723
<i>Quiet it down, moron! Just talk normally!</i>

29
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:46,601
<i>But it's important
to make a good first impression.</i>

30
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:50,396
<i>Your regular voice is loud already!
Do you want complaints from the neighbors?</i>

31
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:53,983
What the hell?
Things were just gettin' good.

32
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,693
What are those bastards doing?

33
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:58,238
Come on! Let's get this going again!

34
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:05,370
<i>What happened? The air's stiff...</i>

35
00:04:05,453 --> 00:04:07,622
<i>Who is this guy?</i>

36
00:04:08,206 --> 00:04:09,415
ON AIR

37
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:12,001
<i>Well, let's get back to it.</i>

38
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:17,006
This is the Bofurin rep, Hajime Umemiya.

39
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:20,593
<i>This guy is Furin's top!</i>

40
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,596
<i>The strongest guy in Furin!</i>

41
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,270
<i>Sorry! I forgot what I was gonna say!</i>

42
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:32,647
<i>Oh, right!</i>

43
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:36,776
<i>You guys better enjoy your youth!
That's right, youth!</i>

44
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:38,528
YOUTH

45
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:41,239
<i>You guys made it to high school,
after all!</i>

46
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:44,284
<i>Go make loads of memories
and live a meaningful school life!</i>

47
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:47,120
<i>Like going to the beach or the mountains!</i>

48
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:48,913
<i>By the way, I'm a beach guy myself!</i>

49
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:50,957
<i>Wow, I really couldn't care less.</i>

50
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:54,294
<i>All right! Let's all go to
the beach this summer!</i>

51
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:55,878
<i>Let's chow on some shaved ice!</i>

52
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,880
Shaved ice?

53
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:01,467
You got a problem with that?

54
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:03,219
Nothing! Nothing at all!

55
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:07,557
I am honored to hear the teachings
of your great god and savior!

56
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:11,102
<i>Ah, right. I said "everyone" out of habit,</i>

57
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:14,897
<i>but with this many people,
some of you may not get along well.</i>

58
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,816
<i>A lot's gonna happen from now on, too.</i>

59
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:20,278
<i>Well, I doubt anyone will be
punching each other on the first day!</i>

60
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:21,195
STARE

61
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,155
RUB RUB

62
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:25,199
<i>I'm not asking y'all to be best buds,
but try to behave, 'kay?</i>

63
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:28,411
You can wipe blood off your nose,
but we all saw you fighting.

64
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:31,581
What the heck? He was
the one who attacked me first!

65
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:35,835
<i>And also, I gotta say this
at the very least...</i>

66
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,087
All of you...

67
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,839
<i>Protect our town.</i>

68
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:45,261
<i>We're given the name "Bofurin,"
"Chime of the Wind Breaker."</i>

69
00:05:45,344 --> 00:05:49,057
{\an8}<i>Live up to that name and protect
the people, the things, and the memories</i>

70
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:51,392
{\an8}<i>of everything that's important to you!</i>

71
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,479
{\an8}<i>That's the one and only rule here.</i>

72
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:55,563
Yes, sir!

73
00:05:56,898 --> 00:05:59,776
<i>That's all!
I'm leaving the rest to you guys!</i>

74
00:05:59,859 --> 00:06:02,653
<i>All right, I'm done!
Let's grab something to eat!</i>

75
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:04,405
<i>The mic is still on!</i>

76
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:07,533
<i>It's not like he's right in front of us...</i>

77
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:10,119
<i>But why does it feel like
everyone's united?</i>

78
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:13,706
<i>Can someone make this happen
just by being good at fighting?</i>

79
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:15,374
<i>Umemiya...</i>

80
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,043
<i>What sort of guy is he?</i>

81
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,255
Hey, you two!
Don't you need to make up now?

82
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:23,007
{\an8}I know! How about you shake hands?

83
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:23,925
{\an8}SQUEEZE

84
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:26,135
{\an8}To settle this! Like proper youth!

85
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:27,053
{\an8}What?

86
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:31,766
Why do I have to do it with him? Besides,
we haven't settled! We're still fighting!

87
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:33,976
And he's the one who attacked me first!

88
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,229
Sakura-san, why is your face red?

89
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:39,232
As someone who strives for the top,

90
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:41,484
this should be trivial for you, right?

91
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:47,281
Sugishita-kun, what do you think
Umemiya-san is going to say,

92
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:49,867
if he hears you attacked your classmate?

93
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:04,632
<i>We're really going to do a handshake?</i>

94
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:06,759
<i>For real?</i>

95
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:10,304
Sakura-san! Hurry and take his hand!

96
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:13,641
<i>I just gotta grab his hand, right?</i>

97
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:16,769
<i>Not punching him back or smack him away...</i>

98
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:20,398
<i>Touching someone for
something other than fighting...</i>

99
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,902
<i>feels really weird.</i>

100
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:32,160
Nice, nice! Now this is youth!

101
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,077
CLENCH

102
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:34,537
<i>What's so nice about this?</i>

103
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:37,290
<i>What is he, a gorilla?</i>

104
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:42,253
Sakura-san!

105
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:44,005
That hurts! What are you doi...

106
00:07:44,088 --> 00:07:48,009
You're really somethin'!
You actually managed to hit Sugishita!

107
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:49,802
That kick was crazy, too!

108
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,429
You're so flexible, huh?

109
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:53,973
I bet he can walk while doing the bridge!

110
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:56,726
-Hey, I can do that!
<i>-But come to think of it,</i>

111
00:07:56,934 --> 00:08:00,897
<i>things like this keep happening
ever since I came to this town...</i>

112
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:08,654
Hey, why are you all quiet?

113
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:11,991
You didn't strangle him, did you?

114
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,245
As if I'd go down that easily!

115
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:21,501
<i>A human body is a lot
warmer than I thought...</i>

116
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:23,878
Hey, you guys!

117
00:08:23,961 --> 00:08:26,255
Get your butts outside. Come on.

118
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:29,634
Huh? We just got inside the classroom.

119
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:30,801
Also, who are you?

120
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:35,640
Sakura-san, that part is uneven!

121
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:36,766
<i>What...</i>

122
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:38,809
I got some extra paint.

123
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:39,769
<i>...is this?</i>

124
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:42,647
Nirei-kun, you're so good at painting.

125
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:44,398
Do you think so?

126
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:47,401
<i>What is happening?</i>

127
00:08:55,993 --> 00:08:57,328
30 MINUTES AGO

128
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,913
What now?

129
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:01,832
We just got to the classroom.

130
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,668
Shut up!

131
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:06,879
Don't just stand there chatting!
Get your butts out to the field!

132
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:10,466
I'm gonna get yelled at
if you little punks are late!

133
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,926
<i>He rolls his tongue a lot...</i>

134
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,844
What's keeping y'all so long?

135
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:22,061
It's been seven minutes, 48 seconds,
and 26 milliseconds!

136
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:25,147
Even preschoolers can
move faster than this!

137
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:29,318
<i>He even counts to the milliseconds?
He's so particular.</i>

138
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,489
He's from yesterday...

139
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,700
Sakura-san, you know him?

140
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,744
Yesterday, when I saved
that girl from the café.

141
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,746
You mean Kotoha-san?

142
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:41,956
WHRRR

143
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,209
WHIZZING

144
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,130
That hurts, man! What are you do...

145
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:54,010
I told you not to tell anyone
that Kotoha-chan was there too!

146
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:57,847
-Gross! Keep your spit to yourself!
-You really don't get it, do you?

147
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,558
-I wonder what they're talking about.
-Yeah, I wonder.

148
00:10:00,641 --> 00:10:06,772
I told you it'll be such a pain in the ass
if he finds out Kotoha-chan was in danger!

149
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:11,027
Anyway, Kotoha-chan wasn't there.

150
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:13,362
And don't tell anyone
what happened yesterday!

151
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:15,114
Or else...

152
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:17,867
GASKUN 10
HEARTBURN RELIEF

153
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:20,620
-I'll throw up blood.
-Huh?

154
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,079
Good grief.

155
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,876
I have no idea why you'd
come here from outta town,

156
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:31,130
but you've ended up
under one hell of a captain.

157
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:32,965
Huh?

158
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,262
Sakura-san, what were you two
talking about?

159
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:39,305
Nothin'.

160
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:42,141
What? Then, what was he like?

161
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:44,518
A weirdo who was yellin' out of nowhere,

162
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,812
started hurtin', and took a Gaskun 10.

163
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:48,147
Gaskun 10?

164
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,607
A stomach medicine?

165
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,609
Why are you writing that down?

166
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:52,985
"Why"?

167
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:57,990
Hiragi-san is one of the
Four Kings of Bofurin!

168
00:10:58,074 --> 00:10:59,617
Four Kings?

169
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,785
REPRESENTATIVE
FOUR KINGS

170
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:05,247
Umemiya-san's the top of Bofurin
and under him are the Four Kings.

171
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:11,045
Each one of them fulfills the role of
captain to one class in each grade.

172
00:11:11,128 --> 00:11:14,090
So we're kinda like team one?

173
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:15,383
Since we're in class one.

174
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:16,342
Oh, not really.

175
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:19,929
<i>Bofurin's Four Kings takes
after the Four Heavenly Kings.</i>

176
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:26,185
<i>So starting from team one, they're called
the Tamon, Jikoku, Zojo, and Komoku teams.</i>

177
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:28,062
<i>We're part of the Tamon team.</i>

178
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:30,564
Split up into a group of four or five.

179
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:35,027
Each group will have
a second or third-year in it.

180
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:39,031
They'll be leading you,
so follow their instructions carefully.

181
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:41,409
Come on, let's go.

182
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:43,786
Go where? For what?

183
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,667
<i>To patrol the town.</i>

184
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,546
Patrolling aside...

185
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,256
{\an8}why do I have to be with <i>him?</i>

186
00:11:55,339 --> 00:11:56,173
{\an8}IGNORING

187
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:58,008
Didn't I tell you already?

188
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:01,387
Umemiya told me to keep my eye on you two.

189
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:04,432
You two are coming with me.
Umemiya's orders.

190
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:07,560
In fact, you two already
got into a fight, didn't you?

191
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:11,814
{\an8}We didn't! He tried to punch me,
so I just kicked him away!

192
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,319
Enough! Just walk and
keep a distance, okay?

193
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:20,698
-He's like a preschool teacher.
-Who're you callin' a teacher?

194
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:24,702
Also, you said patrollin',
but all we do is walk around.

195
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:26,745
If we're supposed to protect the town,

196
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:30,583
wouldn't it be better to just look
for the bad guys to beat instead?

197
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:31,709
You moron.

198
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:35,296
That's called attacking, not protecting.

199
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:36,297
Huh?

200
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:39,341
Walking around town serves a purpose.

201
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:45,806
Just by showin' up in our uniforms,
small teams are gonna stay far away.

202
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:50,019
<i>We fight to protect.</i>

203
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:53,022
There's no need for us
to pick a fight ourselves.

204
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,819
What's that supposed to mean?
That's so boring.

205
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:02,573
You're the boring one for
only finding joy in fist-fights!

206
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,077
Whoa, hey! Granny!

207
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:09,330
Stop it! It's dangerous!

208
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:11,665
You guys get over here!

209
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:13,918
Man, you guys are a lot of help!

210
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,046
They keep painting on the wall
each time we erase it.

211
00:13:17,129 --> 00:13:19,507
There are a lot less of them now, though.

212
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:20,883
It's nothing, sir.

213
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,343
What the hell is this?

214
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:25,054
This is par for the course
for Bofurin members, too.

215
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:27,681
Hey, owner!

216
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:29,475
We're done over here.

217
00:13:29,558 --> 00:13:31,143
Man, thank you so much!

218
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:32,061
NICE AND WARM

219
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,312
Here, take this.

220
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:34,605
Thanks!

221
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,482
Thank you!

222
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:37,650
TAIYAKI WAFFLE CAKE

223
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:46,158
You're not having fun unless it's a fight?

224
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,619
It's not that I don't get it.

225
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:51,914
We were all like that before.

226
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:53,332
But...

227
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:57,169
<i>talking with people
and being needed by them...</i>

228
00:13:58,128 --> 00:14:00,506
that kinda stuff can be pretty fun, too.

229
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:15,312
{\an8}IZAKAYA ASAGAO
BEER, YAKITORI, HOT POT

230
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:30,536
<i>Is it a restaurant district beyond here?</i>

231
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:32,788
<i>Dog?</i>

232
00:14:33,497 --> 00:14:35,249
What an ugly mutt.

233
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:36,375
Sakura-san!

234
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:41,005
You shouldn't say that!
We don't know if those guys are close!

235
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:42,214
Those guys?

236
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:47,136
<i>We're right at the border between
Bofurin and another team's turf.</i>

237
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:50,472
<i>We mustn't cause any trouble
past this tunnel at any cost!</i>

238
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:52,892
<i>Just like how every country
has its own laws,</i>

239
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:55,477
<i>our rules here don't mean
a thing over there.</i>

240
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:58,981
<i>The team that controls the turf
beyond this point is...</i>

241
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:03,235
{\an8}<i>The devotees of power, Shishitoren!</i>

242
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:06,447
Huh, "the devotees of power"?

243
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,744
Not bad. I like the sound of that.

244
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:13,287
Stop right there!

245
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,583
That's San Middle's uniform!

246
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:20,377
What are you doing over there?
Hurry and get over here!

247
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:24,590
Behind him!

248
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:27,676
That orange baseball jacket...
It's Shishitoren!

249
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:31,305
<i>Dammit! He's not gonna make it
past the tunnel!</i>

250
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,742
Hey, bastard. Get outta the way.

251
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:53,577
Why did they do that?

252
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:56,997
Taking on a member of
another team on their turf...

253
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:00,417
What are you talking about?
If this guy is one of us...

254
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:02,753
then they're the ones who struck first!

255
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:04,046
Wha...

256
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,422
Wha...

257
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:09,301
What are you two doing?

258
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,762
I'll take care of the rest.
Get back over there.

259
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:12,680
IGNORING

260
00:16:12,763 --> 00:16:13,639
Listen to me!

261
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,685
What are you doing, man?

262
00:16:19,061 --> 00:16:21,563
{\an8}Well, crap. He's completely knocked out.

263
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:24,984
{\an8}He went down with just one kick. Lame.

264
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:27,486
<i>What's wrong with them?</i>

265
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,780
<i>Aren't they on the same team?</i>

266
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:36,745
Hey, what's with all this?

267
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:41,750
I saw one of our guys runnin' by,

268
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:44,503
so I came all the way here.

269
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:47,756
Out of all people to show up,
it just had to be him?

270
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:52,720
Shishitoren's second-in-command,
Jo Togame!

271
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,473
What are Furin guys doing here?

272
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:02,855
Huh? Saruwatari? What happened to you?

273
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,983
<i>What's up with this guy?</i>

274
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:10,779
That guy was chasin' one of our own.

275
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:15,242
Oh, it's Hiragi.

276
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:16,952
Hello!

277
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:20,539
<i>Why is he talking so slowly?
It's getting on my nerves!</i>

278
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:22,541
Say...

279
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:26,295
did those guys do this?

280
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:30,174
Seems like this guy's something special.

281
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:32,009
Ouch...

282
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:34,970
You bastards! Are you screwing with us?

283
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:37,765
We've got rules not to do crap
on other team's turfs!

284
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:41,018
Past this damn track
is Shishitoren's turf!

285
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:43,896
Don't act all high into our turf...

286
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:55,365
"Our turf"?

287
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:58,452
But you lost.

288
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:03,082
That means you're weak.

289
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,835
You know already, don't you?

290
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:09,755
Weaklings...

291
00:18:10,839 --> 00:18:11,924
Stop it!

292
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:14,551
Huh? What?

293
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:17,805
Isn't he one of your guys?

294
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:19,556
Huh?

295
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,559
Who?

296
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:24,645
Surely not this guy.

297
00:18:24,728 --> 00:18:26,563
Cuz he lost.

298
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:31,110
Losing means you're weak.

299
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:37,658
And the weak don't belong in Shishitoren.

300
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:40,452
How can they?

301
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:45,707
I heard the rumors, but they really
don't seem like the friendly type.

302
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:47,459
Lame.

303
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:51,463
You call yourself "devotees of power"
and this what you do?

304
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:56,677
Beatin' up weaklings is
what power means to you?

305
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:59,596
And here I thought you guys
would be kinda fun.

306
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,598
What a letdown.

307
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:09,231
A letdown, huh?

308
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:14,278
Hey, can you believe what he said?
Should we kill him?

309
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:17,573
Ah, don't worry about that.

310
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,700
More importantly...

311
00:19:21,034 --> 00:19:24,705
Look at your hair.
It's like an Othello board.

312
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:26,206
Huh? You only noticed now?

313
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:30,210
Also, dude, you talk way too fast.

314
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,838
Huh? You're just slow!

315
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,340
See?

316
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:38,093
I can't hear a thing you say...

317
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:40,429
It's getting on my nerves.

318
00:19:41,763 --> 00:19:43,849
All right. I've decided.

319
00:19:43,932 --> 00:19:47,686
I'm gonna pummel you up on a proper stage.

320
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:51,982
I remember your face now.

321
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:54,985
I'll see you again, Othello-kun.

322
00:19:57,654 --> 00:19:58,989
Othello, my ass.

323
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:02,451
Hold up! What have you two done?

324
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,954
You have totally provoked a war!

325
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:07,706
This will be a war!

326
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:10,709
There, there. Calm down, Nirei-kun.

327
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:13,962
{\an8}I missed my cue to interrupt you guys,

328
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:17,674
but after looking at that,
I'm glad I didn't.

329
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:20,719
Hiragi-san, please follow
the daily dose instructions...

330
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:24,056
Besides, if you didn't stir him up
at the end there,

331
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,767
we could've gotten away with that kick!

332
00:20:28,685 --> 00:20:31,647
Togame ain't that easygoing.

333
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:35,651
<i>Among the guys in Shishitoren,
he's particular about their territory.</i>

334
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:37,736
<i>He wouldn't have let us go that easily.</i>

335
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:38,820
{\an8}Is that so?

336
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:39,738
{\an8}DISAPPOINTED

337
00:20:39,821 --> 00:20:42,532
What's done is done.

338
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:46,370
Besides, I should've been
the first one to step in.

339
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:47,621
Sorry.

340
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,749
Let's head back to school now.

341
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:53,252
You're from San Middle...

342
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,837
I'm Sasaki.

343
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,506
You should come with us.

344
00:20:58,715 --> 00:21:00,968
We gotta report everything to Umemiya.

345
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:11,311
<i>Does he hate reporting
to Umemiya that badly?</i>

346
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:15,565
<i>He sounded pretty friendly
on the announcement, though.</i>

347
00:21:16,191 --> 00:21:17,401
<i>Umemiya...</i>

348
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:20,112
<i>What kind of guy is he?</i>

349
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:30,289
What is this?

350
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,499
Wow!

351
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:35,002
Umemiya.

352
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:38,463
<i>The top of Furin!
The strongest in the school!</i>

353
00:21:39,589 --> 00:21:42,926
Oh, Hiragi! Look at this!

354
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:46,722
The eggplants and green peppers
are growing strong!

355
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:50,267
We can have a BBQ
with everyone in the summer!

356
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:54,771
<i>He's like an elementary school kid.</i>

357
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:57,858
<i>Is he... strong?</i>

358
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:36,456
Still, though. What should
we do about this desk?

359
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:38,708
Why are you asking me that?

360
00:23:38,792 --> 00:23:40,335
I didn't break it.

361
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:45,674
But it all started because
you agitated Sugishita-san.

362
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:48,260
Whose side are you on?

363
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:50,178
You go say that to him!

364
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:53,014
Hey, Sugishita! Hey!

365
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:58,812
That bastard! He's pretending to sleep!

